# Codex Writer Findings ‚Äî StaffOrdersMobile
Chain: staffordersmobile-260331-044239-b1e5

## Findings
1. [P1] Fix 1 not implemented: `–í —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–µ` still renders as one flat list ‚Äî `OrderGroupCard` still derives `inProgressOrders` as a single array and renders `inProgressOrders.map(...)` behind one boolean `inProgressExpanded` toggle instead of stage-based sub-groups. The required `orderStages` prop is missing from both the component signature and the parent call site, so there is no way to sort sub-groups by stage order or auto-expand the stage closest to finish. Evidence: `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1301-1320`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1455`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1838-1895`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3964-3984`. FIX: add `orderStages={sortedStages}` at the `OrderGroupCard` call site, accept `orderStages = []` in `OrderGroupCard`, build `subGroups` from `inProgressOrders`, replace the single internal expand state with per-sub-group state, and render stage sub-sections with the required flatten rule when only one stage is active.

2. [P1] Fix 2 not implemented: finish-adjacent custom stages still show `‚Üí [finish stage]` ‚Äî in the stage-mode branch of `getStatusConfig`, `actionLabel` is still always derived as `nextStage ? \`‚Üí ${getStageName(nextStage, t)}\` : null`. That means an order on the stage immediately before the finish stage will still render `‚Üí –í—ã–¥–∞–Ω –≥–æ—Å—Ç—é` instead of `–í—ã–¥–∞—Ç—å`, and Fix 1's subgroup CTA text will inherit the wrong label as well. Evidence: `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:3017-3033`. FIX: in the stage-mode branch, compute `nextIsFinish` from `nextStage.internal_code === 'finish'` or last-index detection, then set `actionLabel` to `nextIsFinish ? '–í—ã–¥–∞—Ç—å' : \`‚Üí ${getStageName(nextStage, t)}\`` without changing the fallback `STATUS_FLOW` branch.

3. [P1] Fix 3A not implemented: dish items are still comma-joined in all three `OrderGroupCard` sections ‚Äî the `–ù–û–í–´–ï`, `–ì–û–¢–û–í–û –ö –í–´–î–ê–ß–ï`, and `–í –Ý–ê–ë–û–¢–ï` order rows still use `orderItems.map(...).join(', ')`, so dishes remain collapsed into one line instead of separate wrapped rows. On a 375px mobile viewport this keeps the old dense layout the fix was supposed to remove. Evidence: `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1757-1760`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1821-1824`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1882-1885`. FIX: replace each joined string block with the required vertical list markup (`space-y-0.5`, one dish per row, `¬∑ {dish_name} √ó{quantity}`), keeping the loading placeholder when items are absent.

4. [P1] Fix 3B not implemented: per-order action buttons are still in the card header instead of the footer ‚Äî each `OrderGroupCard` section still renders the action button inline next to the badge in the upper row, and there is no footer action area after the items list. This violates the required card structure and keeps the CTA visually adjacent to order metadata rather than clearly separated below the dish rows. Evidence: `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1745-1753`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1809-1817`, `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx:1870-1877`. FIX: remove the three header-level inline buttons and add the footer action block after the items list in each section, using the existing `config` variable and `handleBatchAction([order])` handler.

